    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>There are two ways to remove relationships in CWRC-Writer. </cmd>
                <choices id="choices_nh1_ss2_np">
                    <choice>Right-click on the entity that you would like to delete. Click on the
                        <cmdname>Remove Relation</cmdname> option that pops up. <image placement="break"
                            href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A4701972c-649c-482d-93a9-010a62a88ae5/datastream/OBJ/view"
                            id="image_zy1_vs2_np" align="center"/></choice>
                </choices>
                <choices id="choices_opf_ws2_np">
                    <choice>At the bottom of the "Relationship Column" there is a button called
                        <cmdname>Remove Relation</cmdname>. Select the relationship that you would like to delete and
                        click on that button.<image placement="break"
                            href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A9e5a9558-b3df-452b-8966-f0ccdeef82cc/datastream/OBJ/view"
                            id="image_dfq_1t2_np" align="center" height="6in" width="3in"/></choice>
                </choices>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result>This will remove any relationships that you have added to your
            document.     
